    • Constructor Detail

      • StdMissingAttributeDetail

        public StdMissingAttributeDetail(MissingAttributeDetail missingAttributeDetail)
        Creates a new immutable StdMissingAttributeDetail that wraps the given MissingAttributeDetail. The caller agrees not to modify the MissingAttributeDetail as long as the new StdMissingAttributeDetail refers to it.
        Parameters:
        missingAttributeDetail - the MissingAttributeDetail to wrap in the new StdMissingAttributeDetail.

      • StdMissingAttributeDetail

        public StdMissingAttributeDetail(Identifier categoryIn,
                         Identifier attributeIdIn,
                         Identifier dataTypeIdIn,
                         java.lang.String issuerIn,
                         java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> attributeValuesIn)
        Creates a new immutable StdMissingAttributeDetail with the given Identifiers for the XACML Category, AttributeId, and DataType of the missing Attribute, and the given String Issuer. If not null, the Collection of AttributeValues is copied into the new StdMutableMissingAttributeDetail.
        Parameters:
        categoryIn - the Identifier representing the XACML Category of the missing Attribute
        attributeIdIn - the Identifier representing the XACML AttributeId of the missing Attribute
        dataTypeIdIn - the Identifier representing the XACML DataType of the missing AttributeValue
        issuerIn - the String representing the XACML Issuer (may be null)
        attributeValuesIn - the Collection of AttributeValues representing the expected AttributeValues for the missing Attribute

        public java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> getAttributeValues()
        Description copied from interface: MissingAttributeDetail

The Collection returned should not be modified. Implementations are free to use unmodifiable Collections to enforce this.
